snippet.textDisplay:
I had given up on call of duty but this renewed my interest and as I was trying to play the game, I found out that windows 8 is not supported...

I wanna keep windows 8.1 and not upgrade to windows 10 because windows 10 has its own problems and I don't wanna downgrade to windows 7 just to freaking play call of duty warzone, I never thought anything would be any worse than games being exclusive to certain game clients but here we are, in a way this is exclusive to certain OS...

I know the reason is Directx12 is not supported but you honestly should have just stuck with Directx11. Awful planning on their part.
